OL,7,FMotorists are three times more at risk
OL,8,Fof being involved in an accident if
OL,9,Fthey break down on so-called smart
OL,10,Fmotorways without a hard shoulder, new
OL,11,Ffigures show.
OL,13,FA report by National Highways revealed
OL,14,Fthat, in three out of five schemes,
OL,15,Fincidents involving people being
OL,16,Fkilled or seriously injured (KSI)
OL,17,Fduring breakdowns increased on smart
OL,18,Fmotorway stretches where the hard
OL,19,Fshoulder was removed.
